22/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- German Defence Minister Peter Struk said on Thursday (21 August) that the he expects Concordia, the EU military mission in Macedonia, to continue until the spring of 2004. 
Under the present agreement, the mandate expires on 15 December.
In other news Thursday, Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski and Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva met to discuss progress in the EU integration process. 
All agreed more must be done to fight crime and corruption. 
(A1 TV, MIA - 21/08/03)
